ent, the 1500-meter freestyle.\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 976, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wednesday#Paris2024pic.twitter.com\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 842}, {\"ngram\": \"Katie\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 877}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 925}, {\"ngram\": \"her signature event\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1500-meter freestyle\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 974}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is an event shehas not lost in14 years, and don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t expect her to lose that streak in Paris.\\u00c2 A win would result in her 12th career Olympic medal, which would tie for most of any U.S. woman in Olympic history, trailing only Michael Phelps\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s mark of 28.\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1237, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 993}, {\"ngram\": \"in14 years\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1020}, {\"ngram\": \"don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1033}, {\"ngram\": \"that streak\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1064}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1073}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1075}, {\"ngram\": \"A win\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1081}, {\"ngram\": \"her 12th career Olympic medal\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1127}, {\"ngram\": \"any U.S. woman\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1171}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic history\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1190}, {\"ngram\": \"only Michael\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1213}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Keep in mind that the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 1500 free was not an Olympic event until Tokyo in 2021, or else Ledecky would have even more medals to her name.\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1311, \"end\": 1316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9981212885405205, \"rank\": 0.0018822454714542685, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedi